<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="69" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,505,675]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">
This leafhopper is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Matsumura" authorityYear="1932" box="[596,743,505,531]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Igutettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulverosus">
<emphasis box="[596,743,505,531]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">I. pulverosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the features of male genitalia: pygofer broadly rounded caudad and having small dorsal process, aedeagal shaft bearing paired serrated flanges near middle of latero-ventral side and ventral process near basally, and so on. Body length: 
<specimenCount box="[905,926,578,604]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
<quantity box="[934,1073,577,604]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="4.8" metricValueMin="4.2" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="4.8" valueMin="4.2">4.2–4.8 mm</quantity>
; 
<specimenCount box="[1085,1106,578,604]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
4.7–5.0 mm (
<bibRefCitation author="Dworakowska, I." pageId="6" pageNumber="69" pagination="97 - 139" refId="ref6637" refString="Dworakowska, I. (1993 b) Fusiplata Ahmed and some other Dikraneurini (Insects, Auchenorrhyncha, Cicadellidae: Typhlocybinae). Entomologische Abhandlungen Staatliches Museum fur Tierkunde Dresden, 55 (7), 97 - 139." type="journal article" year="1993">Dworakowska, 1993b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
